FBIS4-19957 "drweu079_j_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-079 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY League Backs Berlusconi as Prime Minister League Backs Berlusconi as Prime Minister LD2304103494 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 0938 GMT 23 Apr 94 LD2304103494 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Italian BFN [Excerpt] A delegation from the Northern League told President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro that Forza Italia leader Silvio Berlusconi should be appointed prime minister. The League also asked for guarantees to prevent possible conflicts of [Berlusconi's business] interest. To this end Northern League leader Umberto Bossi said that the Northern League should control key ministeries. Bossi ruled out any other possible candidates. [passage omitted]
